  "source_data_quality_note": "Source MD is widefield-fluorescence boilerplate. Physics grounded in Scarcelli-Yun 2008 confocal Brillouin; Scarcelli et al. 2015 nat. meth. Brillouin microscopy of the eye; Prevedel-Diz-Munoz-Tanaka 2019 Brillouin biomed review; Antonacci-Beck 2020 recent review.",
  "E": {
    "description": "Thermally-populated acoustic phonons at frequency f_B = 2*n*V*sin(theta/2)/lambda scatter incident photons inelastically via Bragg condition. Brillouin shift f_B (GHz) encodes elastic modulus M = rho*V^2. A narrow-linewidth laser (~1 MHz) + high-resolution spectrometer (VIPA/FPA/triple Tandem Fabry-Perot) resolves the Brillouin peak.",
    "forward_model": "I(r, f) = I_Rayleigh * delta(0) + I_Brillouin * Lorentzian(f - f_B(r), Gamma_B(r)) + n",
    "world_state_x": "Elastic-modulus map M(r) (via V), attenuation Gamma_B(r), refractive index n(r)",
    "observation_y": "Spectrum y(r, f) at each confocal voxel",
    "physical_parameters_theta": [
      "Laser wavelength lambda, linewidth",
      "Scattering angle theta (0 or 180 backscatter typical)",
      "Spectrometer finesse F_eff, free spectral range",
      "Integration time tau per voxel",
      "Laser-power-induced heating (dT/dt)",
      "Refractive-index mismatch (assumed or measured)"
    ]
  },
